Pancreatic solid pseudopapillary tumor--report of three cases. Three cases of young females with pancreatic solid pseudopapillary tumor (SPT) were reported. They were referred to Department of Gastroenterology, because of the ultrasonographical finding of the pancreatic tale tumor. In all presented cases, proper diagnosis was made preoperatively. The patients underwent surgical treatment, and remain symptoms-free with no features of recurrence of the disease (follow-up from 6 to 36 months).